{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"The request sent to the external API always includes the complete list of valid taxonomy labels.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"A pure unit mock can miss regressions in request assembly across prompt-builder + API client wiring (MOCK-MISS). No real model behavior is required, but the serialized outbound payload must be validated at module boundaries.","test_description":"Wire the real classifier module with a fake in-process API adapter (or local stub transport) and capture the outgoing request. Assert the taxonomy section contains every configured label exactly once for multiple taxonomy configurations.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.35,"Integration":0.55,"System":0.08,"Agentic":0.02,"Workflow":0.0}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"When the API returns a label that is not in the taxonomy, the module returns \"unknown\".","minimum_level":"Unit","justification":"This is deterministic post-processing logic at a local function/object boundary. A unit test with a stubbed API response can directly exercise the guardrail; real I/O is not needed.","test_description":"Call the label-normalization/classification-result handler with a mocked API label outside the taxonomy (e.g., \"medical\"). Assert returned value is exactly \"unknown\" and no unexpected label is forwarded.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.7,"Integration":0.25,"System":0.03,"Agentic":0.02,"Workflow":0.0}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"The classification result for the same document is the same across repeated calls.","minimum_level":"Agentic","justification":"Correctness depends on real model output stability (LLM-DEP). Mocked/deterministic fakes would hide nondeterminism and make the test always pass (MOCK-HIDE).","test_description":"Run N repeated real API classifications for the same document under production inference settings (same model/config). Assert all returned labels are identical; record any variance as failure.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.02,"Integration":0.05,"System":0.15,"Agentic":0.75,"Workflow":0.03}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"The number of tokens consumed for a typical document stays within the configured per-call budget.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"The real failure boundary is actual token usage against the external API/model tokenizer, which can differ from local estimates (MOCK-HIDE, REAL-INFRA). Requires real HTTP/API usage accounting.","test_description":"Send representative documents through the real API path and read provider-reported prompt/completion/total token usage for each call. Assert total tokens per call do not exceed configured budget.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.05,"Integration":0.25,"System":0.65,"Agentic":0.05,"Workflow":0.0}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"When the API signals that the request rate is too high, the module waits and retries rather than returning an error to the caller.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"Retry behavior often depends on real HTTP status/headers and timing semantics; in-process mocks can miss client-library translation and backoff handling (MOCK-MISS, REAL-INFRA). No model-quality dependence.","test_description":"Use a controllable HTTP test endpoint that returns rate-limit responses (e.g., 429 with retry metadata) before succeeding. Invoke classification once, assert the module delays/retries, then returns success without surfacing the initial rate-limit error.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.03,"Integration":0.3,"System":0.65,"Agentic":0.02,"Workflow":0.0}}]}
